node.text:
I just got back from Khan Tengri Basecamp but before I have time to show you images from the last few days I still have lots of work from my earlier trip about a week ago to the remote south of Kyrgyzstan close to the border with China.
.
You can see Kyzyl Asker (5832m) in all of these photos. In the first photo we found an area with an endless sea of flowers. It was very interesting to see how they grow on basically just stones. We found all kinds of interesting foregrounds in this area, even a skull of a Marco Polo sheep.
.
Kyrgyzstan has neverending possibilities of adventures and I'm happy to explore them always with my good friends of #visitkarakol
.
#kyrgyzstan #mountainlove #mountainadventures #mountainview #mountainlovers #flowerpower #nomadlife #kyrgyzstantravel #sonyalpha #madewithluminar #amazingplaces

node.text:
Here's something a little different. A small series of Edelweiss flowers in the first morning light. Sometimes we forget to look at the little things when we see a giant mountain in front of us.
.
The edelweiss flower(Leontopodium Nivale) is a short lived flower that you can find on high altitudes. It has been used as a symbol for alpinism. You can see millions of them in the mountains of Kyrgyzstan. Seeing them always makes me happy, especially in the golden light.
.
Fun fact: all shots made with the 100-400GM
.
#edelweiss #visitkarakol #flowerphotography #flowerpower #madewithluminar #sonyalpha #sony100400gm #kyrgyzstantravel #visitkyrgyzstan #kyrgyzstan #flowerlovers #flowersofinstagram #flowersmakemehappy #flowerstagram

node.text:
As you can see in my stories I just returned from 7 days in the mountains without any internet. I'll share new images from this adventure soon but before that, here are a bunch of images from before, an afternoon spent in Eltcin valley.
.
I had been here before a couple of years ago. It's such a pleasing valley with lush greens, horses, shepherds and ofcourse the giant mountain (almost 5200m) overlooking the scenery.
.
I really enjoyed spending the day here, walking around and seeing the local shepherds controlling their cattle. 
.
#kyrgyzstan #visitkarakol #mountainlove #mountainview #mountainlovers #mountainlife #nomadlife #kyrgyzstan_trip #sonyalpha #adventuretime #beautifulworld

node.text:
All of these images were taken with the new @sonyxperia 1 III smartphone. I am currently in Kyrgyzstan and already have this phone in my possession for a while. I took all of these images in the last 2 weeks. You might also have seen me photograph tulips with it in the promo :)
.
This smartphone focuses on photography by having a very professional interface. In fact, it’s super similar to that of the Alpha cameras. But the most interesting new feature is the new telephoto lens, that can shoot at 105mm. Of course the phone also shoots RAW. Next to photography the phone has of course many other features, and a beautiful screen to watch your photos and videos. As an #Xperia ambassador I’m always excited to try out the new Sony phones :)
.
#travelbyxperia #sonyxperia1iii #kyrgyzstan
#visitkarakol #smartphonephotography #mobilephotography #kyrgyzstantravel #mobileclick #centralasia #silkroad #mountainlove #outdooradventures

node.text:
Meet peak Palatka 4730m. You can see it towering above the valley all the time when walking in Altyn Arashan. There are multiple ways to get there but each of them takes some effort. Hiking, or driving on difficult roads to say the least. My friends of #visitkarakol climbed this peak multiple times. I have yet to climb my first 'real' peak.
.
#peakpalatka #mountainlove #mountainview #mountainlovers #mountainlife #sonyalpha #adventuretime #treephotography #treesofinstagram #treebrilliance #tree_magic #kyrgyzstan #discoverkyrgyzstan

node.text:
With this series I want to take you on a small visual adventure. This area is called the Boz Uchuk lakes in Kyrgyzstan. You have to do some hiking to get there but once you do, your effort will be rewarded with some beautiful small alpine lakes and nice wild flowers. 
.
We stayed the night here with an extremely starry sky with strong airglow reflecting in the lakes. There's no light pollution here and it's easy to see the milky way with your naked eye.
.
Finding beautiful places like this is what photography and travel is about. And especially in these times, it's appreciated even more.
.
On the road with #visitkarakol 
.

node.text:
This was the 3rd time I have visited this the Skazka Canyon in Kyrgyzstan. The 2 times before I didn’t catch the ultimate light and also wasn’t sure about my composition. So this time, I took some more time to explore the place. This canyon has lots of pointy parts and the whole scene looks like something out of a fantasy movie. By flying the drone carefully around these peaks I found this composition that I really liked. Combined with the spectacular dramatic light I encountered I was finally satisfied with this shot from this place.
.
#visitkarakol #skazkacanyon #visitkyrgyzstan
